g.text: Write a short, whimsical poem. It is composed by a cheerful sloth and extols the virtues of napping.
I'm a sloth, and I'm here to boast,
My napping skills are second to most.
When the day is warm and bright,
I'm snoozing, and not just out of spite.
My head is nestled deep in the trees,
My snore's as loud as a summer's breeze.
My body is still, and I'm not in a rush,
When it comes to napping, I'm the master of hush.
No one can beat me in the art of sleep,
It's my favorite thing to do, when I'm in a heap.
So if you're feeling tired and worn,
Find a tree, and a nap you shall adorn.
